System application displays the properties of each node.

It is an application that is part of Tenet Distribution
( http://tenet.usc.edu )

RUN
----
./system

HELP
----
./system -h

NOTE
----
You will get some error messages regarding MemoryStats when running on MicaZ:

 [Node #] #[ERROR] ERR_NOT_SUPPORTED @ ELEMENT_MEMORYSTATS  (ELEMENT_INDEX 9)
 
But no need to worry. It is a correct behavior for MicaZ.

Output Example
--------------
Number of nodes 2

================================================================================
 ID   NUM  ACTIVE LEDS RADIO RADIO  TIME  NEXT  USED  MAX  TIME
      TASKS TASKS      POWER  CH    SYNCR  HOP  RAM   RAM
================================================================================
  2     1     1     0     5    21     1     1   376   400 84506733
  5     1     1     0     5    21     1     1   376   400 84506733
